What happens when a city you love ï¿½ BOLOGNA, ITALY ï¿½ changes? ?? #Bologna has been my favorite city in Italy for a long time ï¿½ I love the vibe, the food, the culture. And while Iï¿½ve spent a ton of time here, I havenï¿½t been back since 2013. Today when out for a walk, I was sad to see my favorite aperitivo bar and tiramisu spot were gone. And it felt surprising to see ramen, bibimbap and poke spots! And there are a ton of tour groups now, but considering how much work Iï¿½ve been doing for Emilia-Romagna tourism since 2011, more tour groups just means Iï¿½ve done my job! ???? Colson Whitehead once said that you become a New Yorker when the New York you love starts disappearing amidst the new developments. Itï¿½s just a testament to how much you love the city. And Bologna is freaking amazing!!! Iï¿½m so happy to be here amongst the sunshine, the red walls, the 11 AM Lambrusco breaks, and the squacquerone cheese. See my Stories for much more of Bologna. #inEmiliaRomagna ? Have you ever returned to a place that changed?
